<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="worry-v">worry <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'wʌri/    美 /'wɜːri/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>使焦虑；使担忧</strong></h4>
<p>to make sb anxious about sb/sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What worries scientists now is that the African elephant has become an endangered species.
现在令科学家担心的是非洲象已经成为濒危物种。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It worries me that he keeps changing his mind.
我发愁的是他一直在改变注意。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-bother">2.★ <strong>骚扰；烦扰；使不安 (bother)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The noise never seems to worry her.
这噪音似乎从未让她感到厌烦。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t keep worrying him with a lot of silly questions. 
别老用这些愚蠢的问题烦他。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>担心；发愁：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don't worry .We still have plenty of time.
别担心，我们还有很多时间。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Stop worrying about the past and live in the present<strong>worry about</strong>
别担扰过去，活在当下。</p></div></div>